description._content: Description: The venerable headmaster with teaching staff of the Company's school in Ahwaz-1926. Location: Ahwaz, Persia Date: 1926 Description: Mr. J.A. Nichols in conversation with headmaster and teachers at Ahwaz school. Location: Ahwaz, Persia Our Catalogue Reference: Part of CO 1069/714 This image is part of the Colonial Office photographic collection held at The National Archives. Feel free to share it within the spirit of the Commons Please use the comments section below the pictures to share any information you have about the people, places or events shown. We have attempted to provide place information for the images automatically but our software may not have found the correct location.
